            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light"><strong>Bad credit motorcycle loan:</strong> 12.00–22.00% p.a. (specialist lenders, secured preferred)</span></li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Motorcycles depreciate faster than cars on average, which means lenders view them as slightly higher-risk security. This is reflected in rates being marginally higher than car loans for the same borrower profile. However, premium and classic motorcycles (Harley-Davidson, Ducati, BMW GS models) hold their value well and may attract better rates.</p>
        </section>

