            <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">Can I finance a used motorcycle from a private seller?</h3>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100">
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">Yes. Many lenders finance private sale motorcycle purchases. You will need a PPSR check to ensure the bike has no outstanding finance or security interests, and the lender will require the motorcycle details (make, model, year, VIN, odometer). Having pre-approval before negotiating with the seller gives you a confirmed budget and puts you in a strong negotiating position.</p>
