        <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mt-3">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">Do I need a deposit for a motorbike loan?</h3>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100">
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">No deposit is required by most lenders for secured motorcycle loans if you have a strong credit profile. However, a deposit of 10–20% can improve your chances if your credit is not perfect, reduce the amount you borrow (meaning lower repayments and less interest), and help avoid negative equity if the bike depreciates quickly.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mt-3">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">Can I finance motorcycle gear and accessories?</h3>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100">
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">Some lenders allow you to include the cost of helmets, riding gear, and aftermarket accessories in the loan amount — particularly if purchased at the same time as the bike from the same dealer. Limits vary by lender. Adding accessories increases your total borrowing and should be factored into your budget.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mt-3">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">What is the minimum amount for a motorbike loan?</h3>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100">
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">For secured loans (where the bike is collateral), most lenders have a minimum of $5,000–$10,000. For smaller amounts, an unsecured personal loan is typically used. Some online lenders offer smaller secured loans for motorcycles, and credit unions may have lower minimums than major banks.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mt-3">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">Can I get a motorbike loan on a learner permit?</h3>
